

WannaCry Ransomware
What Happened?

WannaCry was a ransomware attack that spread rapidly across the world in May 2017. It encrypted files on infected computers and demanded payment in cryptocurrency.

CIA Triad Affected

Availability

Users could not access their files because they were encrypted.

Impact
More than 200,000 computers infected.
Hospitals and businesses stopped functioning.
Huge financial losses.
Important files became inaccessible.
Prevention
Regular system updates.
Backups of important files.
Antivirus software.
Employee security awareness training.
